{"title_page": "Jean Bruch\u00e9si", "text_new": "'''Jean Bruch\u00e9si''' (9 April 1901 &ndash; 2 October 1979) was a [[Quebec]]ois writer and historian.  He was the president of the [[Royal Society of Canada]] from 1953-4.\n\n==Distinctions and awards==\n* 1949 - [[L\u00e9o-Pariseau Prize]]\n* 1949 - [[Ludger-Duvernay Prize]]\n* 1951 - [[J. B. Tyrrell Medal]]\n* 1959 - [[Medal of the Acad\u00e9mie des lettres du Qu\u00e9bec]]\n\n==Personal life==\nHe married Berthe Denis on 20 June 1930.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.archiv.umontreal.ca/P0000/P0057.html Fonds Jean Bruch\u00e9si] {{in lang|fr}}\n* [http://www.international.gc.ca/department/history-histoire/hplPeople-en.asp?lan=1 Foreign Affairs and International Trade Canada Complete List of Posts]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-npo|pro}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Guilford Bevil Reed]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=President of the [[Royal Society of Canada]]|years=1953\u20131954}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Edgar William Richard Steacie]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bruchesi, Jean}}\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1979 deaths]]\n[[Category:Canadian political scientists]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Royal Society of Canada]]\n[[Category:Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al faculty]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian scientists]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian writers]]\n[[Category:Journalists from Quebec]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian journalists]]\n[[Category:Canadian diplomats]]\n[[Category:Canadian literary critics]]\n[[Category:20th-century Canadian historians]]\n", "text_old": "'''Jean Bruch\u00e9si''' (9 April 1901 &ndash; 2 October 1979) was a [[Quebec]]ois writer and historian.  He was the president of the [[Royal Society of Canada]] from 1953-4.\n\n==Distinctions and awards==\n* 1949 - [[L\u00e9o-Pariseau Prize]]\n* 1949 - [[Ludger-Duvernay Prize]]\n* 1951 - [[J. B. Tyrrell Medal]]\n* 1959 - Medal of the [[Acad\u00e9mie des lettres du Qu\u00e9bec]]\n\n==Personal life==\