{"title_page": "Prince Constantine Alexios of Greece and Denmark", "text_new": "{{Infobox royalty\n|name        = Prince Constantine Alexios\n|image       = Constantine of Grecce.png\n|image_size  = 150px\n|caption     = Prince Constantine in 2015\n|house       = [[House of Gl\u00fccksburg|Gl\u00fccksburg]]\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1998|10|29}}\n|father      = [[Pavlos, Crown Prince of Greece]]\n|mother      = [[Marie-Chantal, Crown Princess of Greece|Marie-Chantal Miller]]\n|religion    =  [[Greek Orthodox]]\n|birth_place = [[Weill Cornell Medical Center]], [[New York City]], U.S.\n}}\n{{Greek Royal Family}}\n'''Prince Constantine Alexios of Greece and Denmark''' ({{lang-el|\u039a\u03c9\u03bd\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2 \u0391\u03bb\u03ad\u03be\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2}}; born 29 October 1998) is a member of the [[Greek royal family]], the eldest son and second child of [[Pavlos, Crown Prince of Greece|Crown Prince Pavlos]] and [[Marie-Chantal, Crown Princess of Greece|Crown Princess Marie-Chantal]] of Greece.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/picturegalleries/royalty/8140454/Kate-Middletons-sister-Pippa-is-tipped-to-be-chief-bridesmaid-but-who-will-join-her-at-the-Royal-Wedding.html?image=6|title=Kate Middleton's sister Pippa is tipped to be chief bridesmaid, but who will join her at the Royal Wedding?|publisher=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=|accessdate=21 June 2018|language=}}</ref> He is second in [[Line of succession to the former Greek throne|line of succession]], after his father, to the former throne of Greece. His paternal grandparents are [[Constantine II of Greece|Constantine II]] and [[Anne-Marie of Denmark]], who were the last [[List of kings of Greece|King]] and [[Queen of the Hellenes]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-17744572.html|title=One Elle of a christening|date=June 8, 2001|work=[[Birmingham Mail]]|access-date=June 21, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620232641/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-17744572.html|archive-date=2018-06-20|url-status=dead|url-access=subscription|via=HighBeam Research}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aol.com/article/entertainment/2016/10/31/move-over-prince-harry-this-young-royal-may-steal-your-mos/21595790/|title=Move over Prince Harry&nbsp;\u2013 this young royal may steal your 'Most Eligible Bachelor' crown|publisher=[[AOL]]|date=31 October 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|author=MARAH ALINDOGAN}}</ref><ref>Debrett's Peerage Limited, 2008 ''Debrett's Peerage and Baronetage'' University of California Press. {{ISBN|9781870520805}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://mad.tv/gnoriste-ta-eggonia-toy-teos-vasilia-tis-elladas-konstantinoy/|title=\u0394\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03ba\u03bf\u03cd\u03ba\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u0388\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b5\u03c2 \"\u03c0\u03c1\u03af\u03b3\u03ba\u03b9\u03c0\u03b5\u03c2\": \u039f\u03b9 \u03b5\u03b3\u03b3\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03af \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c4\u03ad\u03c9\u03c2 \u03b2\u03b1\u03c3\u03b9\u03bb\u03b9\u03ac \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1\u03c2 \u039a\u03c9\u03bd\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5|publisher=[[MAD TV (Greece)]]|date=17 June 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|language=el}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.obozrevatel.com/life/people/82073-zavidnyij-zhenih-grecheskij-prints-konstantin-aleksios-otprazdnoval-18-letie.htm|title=\u0417\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0445: \u0433\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0446 \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d-\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0438\u043e\u0441 \u043e\u0442\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b 18-\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0435|publisher=Obozrevatel|date=2 November 2016|accessdate=24 June 2018|language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.papermag.com/the-new-royals-2564694710.html|title=The New Royals|publisher=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|date=|accessdate=29 August 2018|language=}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nConstantine Alexios was born on 29 October 1998 at [[Weill Cornell Medical Center]] in [[New York City]]. His parents relocated to London in 2004 for their children's education. He was educated at [[Wellington College, Berkshire|Wellington College]] in Berkshire and is currently enrolled in [[Georgetown University]] in Washington D.C.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-4821360/Greek-prince-princess-cousin-start-Georgetown.html|title=Royalty on campus! Greek prince and his princess cousin&nbsp;\u2013 who is Diane Von Furstenburg's granddaughter&nbsp;\u2013 move into dorms at Georgetown to start their freshman year|publisher=[[Daily Mail]]|date=24 August 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018|author=Chris Spargo}}</ref> He is the younger brother of [[Princess Maria-Olympia of Greece and Denmark|Princess Maria-Olympia]] and older brother of [[Prince Achileas-Andreas of Greece and Denmark|Prince Achileas-Andreas]], Prince Odysseas-Kimon, and Prince Aristidis-Stavros. He is second in line to the former Greek throne after his father.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/royalty/2017082541912/prince-william-godson-starts-university/|title=Prince William's godson starts university!|publisher=[[Hello! (magazine)|Hello!]]|date=25 August 2017|accessdate=21 June 2018|author=Ainhoa Barcelona}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.es/estilo/gente/abci-olympia-grecia-triunfo-debut-dentro-sociedad-royal-201805281937_noticia.html|title=Olympia de Grecia triunfa en su debut dentro de la sociedad \"royal\"|publisher=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC.es]]|date=29 May 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.spletnik.ru/buzz/baby/71081-grecheskiy-printc-konstantin-aleksios-chto-my-znaem.html|title=\u0413\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0446 \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d-\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0438\u043e\u0441: \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u044e\u043d\u043e\u0448\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0447\u0430\u0442 \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0446\u0430 \u0413\u0430\u0440\u0440\u0438|publisher=Spletnik Russia|date=2 November 2016|accessdate=24 June 2018|language=ru}}</ref>\n\nThe prince was christened in a [[Greek Orthodox Church|Greek Orthodox]] ceremony at [[St Sophia's Cathedral, London|St. Sophia's Cathedral]], London, on 15 April 1999. His godparents are [[Prince Nikolaos of Greece and Denmark]]; [[Prince Dimitri of Yugoslavia]]; [[Frederik, Crown Prince of Denmark]]; [[Felipe, Prince of Asturias|King Felipe VI of Spain]]; [[Prince William, Duke of Cambridge]]; [[Victoria, Crown Princess of Sweden]]; [[Alexandra von F\u00fcrstenberg|Princess Alexandra zu F\u00fcrstenberg]]; and Doris Robbs. Three of his godparents are prospective monarchs and one is a reigning king.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/the-incredible-life-of-greeces-instagram-famous-prince-2018-6|title=The incredible life of Prince William's Instagram-famous godson, Prince Constantine-Alexios of Greece|publisher=[[Business Insider]]|date=10 June 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|author=Tom Murray}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pressreader.com/singapore/harpers-bazaar-singapore/20180401/284889480989644|title=Prince Constantine-Alexios of Greece and Denmark|publisher=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|date=1 Apr 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|language=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.scmp.com/magazines/style/people-events/article/2150346/meet-prince-williams-instagram-famous-godson-prince|title=Meet Prince William's Instagram-famous godson, Prince Constantine-Alexios of Greece|publisher=[[South China Morning Post]]|date=12 June 2018|accessdate=26 June 2018|language=}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn May 2018, Constantine-Alexios attended a gala dinner to celebrate the 50th birthday of his cousin, [[Crown Prince Frederik of Denmark]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Guest list for the Gala Banquet at Christiansborg Palace, 26 May 2018, on the occasion of HRH The Crown Prince's 50th birthday.|url=http://kongehuset.dk/en/news/guest-list-for-gala-banquet-at-christiansborg-palace|website=Royal House of Denmark}}</ref> Constantine-Alexios is currently a student at [[Georgetown University|Georgetown University.  He started there as a freshman in the fall of 2017]] along with his cousin [[Princess Talita von F\u00fcrstenberg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/tradition/a12798065/is-georgetown-the-new-brown/|title=Is Georgetown the New Brown?|publisher=[[Town & Country (magazine)|Town & Country]]|date=13 October 2017|accessdate=15 July 2018|author=MARC KARIMZADEH}}</ref>She subsequently transferred to NYU which she currently attends. \n\n==Titles, styles, honours, and arms==\n[[File:Arms of a Prince of Greece.svg|thumb|100px|Arms of a Prince of Greece]]\n*29 October 1998&nbsp;\u2013 present: ''His Royal Highness'' Prince Constantine Alexios of Greece and Denmark\n* {{flagicon|Greece|royal}} [[Greek Royal Family]] Grand Cross of the [[Order of the Redeemer]]\n\n==Ancestry==\nOn his father's side he is a member of the [[Greek Royal Family]] and the [[Danish Royal Family]]. Constantine Alexios's [[patrilineal]] great-great-grandfather, [[Constantine I of Greece]], was the son of [[George I of Greece]], whose father was [[Christian IX of Denmark]]. As a male-line descendant of Christian IX, he holds the title of Prince of Denmark.\n\nHis mother is the daughter of American-born British billionaire [[Robert Warren Miller]] and his Ecuadorian wife, Marie Chantal Pesantes. Constantine Alexios's maternal grandfather descends from passengers on the [[Mayflower]] and is connected to the British North American [[American gentry|colonial elite]]. His family claims to descend from [[Henry I of England]], [[Louis IV of France]], and [[William I of Scotland]].<ref name=\"WARGS\">{{cite web|last1=Reitwiesner|first1=William|last2=Otto|first2=Julie|title=Some ancestry of the Miller sisters|url=http://www.wargs.com/royal/miller.html|website=William Addams Reitwiesner Genealogical Services|accessdate=21 June 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070327201420/http://www.wargs.com/royal/miller.html|archivedate=27 March 2007|language=English}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Instagram|alexiosgreece|Constantine Alexios}}\n* [https://www.greekroyalfamily.gr/en/press/press-releases/229-i-vaftisi-tou-konstantinou-alexiou.html Christening of Constantine Alexios]\n\n{{Greek princes}}\n{{Danish princes}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Constantine Alexios}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Georgetown University alumni]]\n[[Category:House of Gl\u00fccksburg (Greece)]]\n[[Category:Members of the Church of Greece]]\n[[Category:Danish princes]]\n[[Category:Greek princes]]\n[[Category:Greek Orthodox Christians from the United States]]\n[[Category:People educated at Wellington College, Berkshire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox royalty\n|name        = Prince Constantine Alexios\n|image       = Constantine of Grecce.png\n|image_size  = 150px\n|caption     = Prince Constantine in 2015\n|house       = [[House of Gl\u00fccksburg|Gl\u00fccksburg]]\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1998|10|29}}\n|father      = [[Pavlos, Crown Prince of Greece]]\n|mother      = [[Marie-Chantal, Crown Princess of Greece|Marie-Chantal Miller]]\n|religion    =  [[Greek Orthodox]]\n|birth_place = [[Weill Cornell Medical Center]], [[New York City]], U.S.\n}}\n{{Greek Royal Family}}\n'''Prince Constantine Alexios of Greece and Denmark''' ({{lang-el|\u039a\u03c9\u03bd\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2 \u0391\u03bb\u03ad\u03be\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2}}; born 29 October 1998) is a member of the [[Greek royal family]], the eldest son and second child of [[Pavlos, Crown Prince of Greece|Crown Prince Pavlos]] and [[Marie-Chantal, Crown Princess of Greece|Crown Princess Marie-Chantal]] of Greece.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/picturegalleries/royalty/8140454/Kate-Middletons-sister-Pippa-is-tipped-to-be-chief-bridesmaid-but-who-will-join-her-at-the-Royal-Wedding.html?image=6|title=Kate Middleton's sister Pippa is tipped to be chief bridesmaid, but who will join her at the Royal Wedding?|publisher=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=|accessdate=21 June 2018|language=}}</ref> He is second in [[Line of succession to the former Greek throne|line of succession]], after his father, to the former throne of Greece. His paternal grandparents are [[Constantine II of Greece|Constantine II]] and [[Anne-Marie of Denmark]], who were the last [[List of kings of Greece|King]] and [[Queen of the Hellenes]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-17744572.html|title=One Elle of a christening|date=June 8, 2001|work=[[Birmingham Mail]]|access-date=June 21, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180620232641/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-17744572.html|archive-date=2018-06-20|url-status=dead|url-access=subscription|via=HighBeam Research}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aol.com/article/entertainment/2016/10/31/move-over-prince-harry-this-young-royal-may-steal-your-mos/21595790/|title=Move over Prince Harry&nbsp;\u2013 this young royal may steal your 'Most Eligible Bachelor' crown|publisher=[[AOL]]|date=31 October 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|author=MARAH ALINDOGAN}}</ref><ref>Debrett's Peerage Limited, 2008 ''Debrett's Peerage and Baronetage'' University of California Press. {{ISBN|9781870520805}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://mad.tv/gnoriste-ta-eggonia-toy-teos-vasilia-tis-elladas-konstantinoy/|title=\u0394\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03ba\u03bf\u03cd\u03ba\u03bb\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u0388\u03bb\u03bb\u03b7\u03bd\u03b5\u03c2 \"\u03c0\u03c1\u03af\u03b3\u03ba\u03b9\u03c0\u03b5\u03c2\": \u039f\u03b9 \u03b5\u03b3\u03b3\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03af \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c4\u03ad\u03c9\u03c2 \u03b2\u03b1\u03c3\u03b9\u03bb\u03b9\u03ac \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1\u03c2 \u039a\u03c9\u03bd\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5|publisher=[[MAD TV (Greece)]]|date=17 June 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|language=el}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.obozrevatel.com/life/people/82073-zavidnyij-zhenih-grecheskij-prints-konstantin-aleksios-otprazdnoval-18-letie.htm|title=\u0417\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0434\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0445: \u0433\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0446 \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d-\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0438\u043e\u0441 \u043e\u0442\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b 18-\u043b\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0435|publisher=Obozrevatel|date=2 November 2016|accessdate=24 June 2018|language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.papermag.com/the-new-royals-2564694710.html|title=The New Royals|publisher=[[Paper (magazine)|Paper]]|date=|accessdate=29 August 2018|language=}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nConstantine Alexios was born on 29 October 1998 at [[Weill Cornell Medical Center]] in [[New York City]]. His parents relocated to London in 2004 for their children's education. He was educated at [[Wellington College, Berkshire|Wellington College]] in Berkshire and is currently enrolled in [[Georgetown University]] in Washington D.C.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-4821360/Greek-prince-princess-cousin-start-Georgetown.html|title=Royalty on campus! Greek prince and his princess cousin&nbsp;\u2013 who is Diane Von Furstenburg's granddaughter&nbsp;\u2013 move into dorms at Georgetown to start their freshman year|publisher=[[Daily Mail]]|date=24 August 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018|author=Chris Spargo}}</ref> He is the younger brother of [[Princess Maria-Olympia of Greece and Denmark|Princess Maria-Olympia]] and older brother of [[Prince Achileas-Andreas of Greece and Denmark|Prince Achileas-Andreas]], Prince Odysseas-Kimon, and Prince Aristidis-Stavros. He is second in line to the former Greek throne after his father.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hellomagazine.com/royalty/2017082541912/prince-william-godson-starts-university/|title=Prince William's godson starts university!|publisher=[[Hello! (magazine)|Hello!]]|date=25 August 2017|accessdate=21 June 2018|author=Ainhoa Barcelona}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abc.es/estilo/gente/abci-olympia-grecia-triunfo-debut-dentro-sociedad-royal-201805281937_noticia.html|title=Olympia de Grecia triunfa en su debut dentro de la sociedad \"royal\"|publisher=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC.es]]|date=29 May 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.spletnik.ru/buzz/baby/71081-grecheskiy-printc-konstantin-aleksios-chto-my-znaem.html|title=\u0413\u0440\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0446 \u041a\u043e\u043d\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d-\u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0438\u043e\u0441: \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u044e\u043d\u043e\u0448\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0447\u0430\u0442 \u043f\u043e\u043f\u0443\u043b\u044f\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0446\u0430 \u0413\u0430\u0440\u0440\u0438|publisher=Spletnik Russia|date=2 November 2016|accessdate=24 June 2018|language=ru}}</ref>\n\nThe prince was christened in a [[Greek Orthodox Church|Greek Orthodox]] ceremony at [[St Sophia's Cathedral, London|St. Sophia's Cathedral]], London, on 15 April 1999. His godparents are [[Prince Nikolaos of Greece and Denmark]]; [[Prince Dimitri of Yugoslavia]]; [[Frederik, Crown Prince of Denmark]]; [[Felipe, Prince of Asturias|King Felipe VI of Spain]]; [[Prince William, Duke of Cambridge]]; [[Victoria, Crown Princess of Sweden]]; [[Alexandra von F\u00fcrstenberg|Princess Alexandra zu F\u00fcrstenberg]]; and Doris Robbs. Three of his godparents are prospective monarchs and one is a reigning king.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/the-incredible-life-of-greeces-instagram-famous-prince-2018-6|title=The incredible life of Prince William's Instagram-famous godson, Prince Constantine-Alexios of Greece|publisher=[[Business Insider]]|date=10 June 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|author=Tom Murray}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pressreader.com/singapore/harpers-bazaar-singapore/20180401/284889480989644|title=Prince Constantine-Alexios of Greece and Denmark|publisher=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|date=1 Apr 2018|accessdate=21 June 2018|language=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.scmp.com/magazines/style/people-events/article/2150346/meet-prince-williams-instagram-famous-godson-prince|title=Meet Prince William's Instagram-famous godson, Prince Constantine-Alexios of Greece|publisher=[[South China Morning Post]]|date=12 June 2018|accessdate=26 June 2018|language=}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn May 2018, Constantine-Alexios attended a gala dinner to celebrate the 50th birthday of his cousin, [[Crown Prince Frederik of Denmark]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Guest list for the Gala Banquet at Christiansborg Palace, 26 May 2018, on the occasion of HRH The Crown Prince's 50th birthday.|url=http://kongehuset.dk/en/news/guest-list-for-gala-banquet-at-christiansborg-palace|website=Royal House of Denmark}}</ref> Constantine-Alexios is currently a student at [[Georgetown University]], along with his cousin [[Princess Talita von F\u00fcrstenberg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/tradition/a12798065/is-georgetown-the-new-brown/|title=Is Georgetown the New Brown?|publisher=[[Town & Country (magazine)|Town & Country]]|date=13 October 2017|accessdate=15 July 2018|author=MARC KARIMZADEH}}</ref>\n\n==Titles, styles, honours, and arms==\n[[File:Arms of a Prince of Greece.svg|thumb|100px|Arms of a Prince of Greece]]\n*29 October 1998&nbsp;\u2013 present: ''His Royal Highness'' Prince Constantine Alexios of Greece and Denmark\n* {{flagicon|Greece|royal}} [[Greek Royal Family]] Grand Cross of the [[Order of the Redeemer]]\n\n==Ancestry==\nOn his father's side he is a member of the [[Greek Royal Family]] and the [[Danish Royal Family]]. Constantine Alexios's [[patrilineal]] great-great-grandfather, [[Constantine I of Greece]], was the son of [[George I of Greece]], whose father was [[Christian IX of Denmark]]. As a male-line descendant of Christian IX, he holds the title of Prince of Denmark.\n\nHis mother is the daughter of American-born British billionaire [[Robert Warren Miller]] and his Ecuadorian wife, Marie Chantal Pesantes. Constantine Alexios's maternal grandfather descends from passengers on the [[Mayflower]] and is connected to the British North American [[American gentry|colonial elite]]. His family claims to descend from [[Henry I of England]], [[Louis IV of France]], and [[William I of Scotland]].<ref name=\"WARGS\">{{cite web|last1=Reitwiesner|first1=William|last2=Otto|first2=Julie|title=Some ancestry of the Miller sisters|url=http://www.wargs.com/royal/miller.html|website=William Addams Reitwiesner Genealogical Services|accessdate=21 June 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070327201420/http://www.wargs.com/royal/miller.html|archivedate=27 March 2007|language=English}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Instagram|alexiosgreece|Constantine Alexios}}\n* [https://www.greekroyalfamily.gr/en/press/press-releases/229-i-vaftisi-tou-konstantinou-alexiou.html Christening of Constantine Alexios]\n\n{{Greek princes}}\n{{Danish princes}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Constantine Alexios}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Georgetown University alumni]]\n[[Category:House of Gl\u00fccksburg (Greece)]]\n[[Category:Members of the Church of Greece]]\n[[Category:Danish princes]]\n[[Category:Greek princes]]\n[[Category:Greek Orthodox Christians from the United States]]\n[[Category:People educated at Wellington College, Berkshire]]\n", "name_user": "2601:204:4000:b670:dcf9:a721:ac17:5b03", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(His cousin Talita isn\u2019t at Georgetown with him anymore. She transferred)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prince_Constantine_Alexios_of_Greece_and_Denmark"}
{"title_page": "30 Hronia Katy Garbi (Live Katrakio 2019)", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name         = 30 Hronia Katy Garbi (Live Katrakio 2019)<br>30 \u03a7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b9\u03b1 \u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae (Live \u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03c1\u03ac\u03ba\u03b5\u03b9\u03bf 2019)\n| type         = Live\n| artist       = [[Katy Garbi]]\n| cover        = 30_Hronia_Live_-_Garbi_Album_Cover_13-04-2020.png\n| border       = yes\n| alt          = \n| released     = April 13, 2020\n| recorded     = September 16, 2019\n| venue        = Katrakio Theater [[Nikaia, Attica|Nikaia]]\n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Pop music|Pop]], [[Modern Laika]], [[Dance music|Dance]]\n| length       = 170:00\n| language     = [[Greek language|Greek]]\n| label        = Panik Records<br>Panik Platinum\n| producer     = Leonidas Tzitzos\n| prev_title   = [[Spase Tous Deiktes]]\n| prev_year    = 2017\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    =\n}}\n\n'''''30 Hronia Katy Garbi (Live Katrakio 2019)''''' ({{lang-el|30 \u03a7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b9\u03b1 \u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae (Live \u039a\u03b1\u03c4\u03c1\u03ac\u03ba\u03b5\u03b9\u03bf 2019)}}; {{lang-en|30 Years Katy Garbi (Live Katrakio 2019)}}) is a live album by popular Greek singer [[Katy Garbi]] recorded in 2019 and released in 2020 by Panik Records. The album is Garbi's second live album; a three-disc compilation of songs performed during a special concert held at the Katrakeio Theater [[Nikaia, Attica|Nikaia]] in honour of Garbi's 30 years of discography.<ref name=HitChannel2020Digital>{{cite web|url=https://www.hit-channel.com/kaiti-garmpi-sold-out-synavlia-30-xronia-diskografia/169535|script-title=el:\u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae: \u0397 sold out \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03b1\u03c5\u03bb\u03af\u03b1 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 30 \u03c7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03b4\u03b9\u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03af\u03b1 (pics) (2019-09-19)|website=Hit-Channel|language=Greek|accessdate=2019-11-03}}</ref> The album features performances by [[Eleni Foureira]], [[Giorgos Papadopoulos]], [[Antonis Remos]], [[Giorgos Sabanis]], Dimitris Schinas, Dionysis Schinas and [[Kostas Tournas]].<ref name=HitChannel2020Digital/>\n\n==Release==\nThe album was first released through digital platforms on April 13, 2020 by Panik Plantinum and licenced by Heart Events.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mikrofwno.gr/2020/04/i-kaiti-garmpi-giortazei-30-chronia-sti-diskografia-me-triplo-live-album/|title=\u0397 \u039a\u03b1\u03af\u03c4\u03b7 \u0393\u03b1\u03c1\u03bc\u03c0\u03ae \u03b3\u03b9\u03bf\u03c1\u03c4\u03ac\u03b6\u03b5\u03b9 30 \u03c7\u03c1\u03cc\u03bd\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03b4\u03b9\u03c3\u03ba\u03bf\u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c6\u03af\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03c4\u03c1\u03b9\u03c0\u03bb\u03cc Live album (2020-04-13)|website=MikrofonoGr|language=Greek|accessdate=2020-04-14}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Disc one\n| extra_column    = Original album\n| title1          = Intro\n| note1           = \n| extra1          = \n| lyrics1         = \n| music1          = \n| length1         = 2:09\n| title2          = Kainourgia Ego\n| note2           = \n| extra2          = [[Kainourgia Ego]]\n| lyrics2         = GML, Thirio\n| music2          = Nikos Antipas\n| length2         = 2:23\n| title3          = Tha Melaholiso\n| note3           = \n| extra3          = [[Arhizo Polemo]]\n| lyrics3         = [[Phoebus (songwriter)|Phoebus]]\n| music3          = Phoebus\n| length3         = 2:33\n| title4          = Ilios De Vgeni An Den Peis Kalimera\n| note4           = \n| extra4          = Non-album\n| lyrics4         = Phoebus\n| music4          = Phoebus\n| length4         = 3:21\n| title5          = Hamena\n| extra5          = [[Arhizo Polemo]]\n| note5           = \n| lyrics5         = Phoebus\n| music5          = Phoebus\n