 Zbekos\n| length20        = 1:09\n| title21         = Mou Leipeis\n| note21          = \n| extra21         = [[Evaisthisies]]\n| lyrics21        = Phoebus\n| music21         = Phoebus\n| length21        = 1:21\n| title22         = Perasmena Ksehasmena\n| note22          = \n| extra22         = [[Arhizo Polemo]]\n| lyrics22        = Giannis Doxas\n| music22         = Charis Andreadis\n| length22        = 3:23\n| title23         = Kalitera I Dio Mas\n| note23          = \n| extra23         = [[Kravgi]]\n| lyrics23        = Natalia Germanou\n| music23         = [[Nikos Karvelas]]\n| length23        = 1:25\n| title24         = Katapliktiko\n| note24          = \n| extra24         = [[Galazio Kai Lefko + Remixes]]\n| lyrics24        = Tasos Vougiatzis\n| music24         = Ilias Pantazopoulos\n| length24        = 1:50\n| title25         = Agkyres\n| note25          = \n| extra25         = [[Doro Theou]]\n| lyrics25        = Eleni Giannatsoulia\n| music25         = Savvas Angin\n| length25        = 1:50\n| title26         = Skorpia\n| note26          = featuring Giorgos Sabanis\n| extra26         = [[Spase Tous Deiktes]]\n| lyrics26        = Nikos Gritsis\n| music26         = Dimitris Kontopoulos\t \n| length26        = 3:40\n| title27         = Spase Tous Deiktes Tou Rologiou\n| note27          = \n| extra27         = [[Spase Tous Deiktes]]\n| lyrics27        = Eleni Giannatsoulia\n| music27         = Giorgos Sabanis\n| length27        = 2:42\n| title28         = Otan Se Hreiazomai\n| note28          = \n| extra28         = [[Apla Ta Pragmata]]\n| lyrics28        = Antonis Pappas\n| music28         = Nikos Terzis\t \n| length28        = 2:35\n| title29         = Outro (Kivotos)\n| note29          = \n| extra29         = [[Evaisthisies]]\n| lyrics29        = Phoebus\n| music29         = Phoebus\t \n| length29        = 2:43\n| total_length    = 170:00\n}}\n\n==Release history==\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Region\n! scope=\"row\"| Date\n! scope=\"row\"| Format\n! scope=\"row\"| Label\n! scope=\"row\"| {{abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| April 13, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| Panik Platinum\n| <ref name=HitChannel2020Digital/>\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Katy Garbi}}\n\n[[Category:Katy Garbi live albums]]\n[[Category:2020 live albums]]\n[[Category:Panik Records albums]]\n[[Category:Greek-language live albums]]\n", "name_user": "CyprusPlace2b", "label": "safe", "comment": "remove hyperlink", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/30_Hronia_Katy_Garbi_(Live_Katrakio_2019)"}
{"title_page": "Will Downing", "text_new": "{{short description|American singer and songwriter|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{BLP sources|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| name                = Will Downing\n| image               =\n| image_size        = \n| landscape          = \n| caption             = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Wilfred Downing \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1963|11|29}}\n| birth_place        = [[Brooklyn, New York]], U.S.\n| genre               = [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]], [[soul music|soul]], [[neo soul]], [[jazz]]\n| occupation        = Singer, songwriter\n| instrument        = Vocals\n| years_active     = 1986\u2013present\n| label                = [[Peak Records|Peak]], [[Hip-O Records|Hip-O]], [[GRP Records|GRP]], [[Mercury Records|Mercury]], [[Motown Records|Motown]], [[PolyGram Records|PolyGram]], [[Island Records|Island]], Sophisticated Soul\n| associated_acts =\n| website            = {{URL|www.willdowning.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Wilfred \"Will\" Downing''' (born November 29, 1963 in [[Brooklyn]], New York) is an American singer and songwriter.<ref name=\"AMG\">{{cite web|last=Wynn |first=Ron |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/will-downing-mn0000960874 |title=Will Downing - Music Biography, Credits and Discography |publisher=AllMusic |date= |accessdate=2013-03-28}}</ref> He is married to singer Audrey Wheeler, who was a member of the R&B group [[Unlimited Touch]].\n\n==Biography==\nDowning enrolled in [[Erasmus Hall High School]] in Brooklyn, New York. Alumni of the school include [[record label]] executives [[Clive Davis]] (who founded [[Arista Records]]), [[Kedar Massenburg]] (who later became president of [[Motown]]), Stephanie Mills and singer [[Barbra Streisand]].<ref>[http://www.blakeradio.com/html/video_lounge/vl_will.shtml ] {{webarchive \n|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070701154909/http://www.blakeradio.com/html/video_lounge/vl_will.shtml |date=July 1, 2007 }}</ref> Downing, who eventually recorded for Motown, graduated with Massenburg in the class of 1981. Downing then attended college at [[Virginia Union University]] in [[Richmond, Virginia]]. In the mid-1980s, he moved back to New York City, and worked on [[album]]s by [[Jennifer Holliday]], [[Kool & the Gang]], [[Gerald Albright]], [[Billy Ocean]], [[Regina Belle]], [[Rachelle Ferrell]] and [[Mica Paris]]. Later he sang with [[Arthur Baker (musician)|Arthur Baker]]'s group, Wally 'Jump' Junior.<ref name=\"AMG\"/> Downing then used Baker as a producer after he signed with [[Island Records]]. In 1988, Downing signed a [[recording contract]] with [[4th & Broadway]] Records, and his first solo album, ''Will Downing'', was released that same year. His version of the [[John Coltrane]] piece, \"[[A Love Supreme]]\",<ref name=\"AMG\"/> reached No.&nbsp;4 on the ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot Dance Club Songs]] [[record chart|chart]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/will-downing-mn0000960874/awards |title=Will Downing - Awards |publisher=AllMusic |date= |accessdate=2013-03-28}}</ref> Downing stayed with 4th & Broadway for just one album and switched to Island Records for his second release, ''Come Together As One'' (1989).<ref name=\"AMG\"/>  Switching labels to [[Mercury Records|Mercury]] for his fourth outing, 1993's ''Love's the Place to Be'', Downing scored his best-selling album to date with about 235,000 copies sold in the United States and over 300,000 copies in the [[United Kingdom|UK]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enotes.com/contemporary-musicians/downing-will-biography |title=Downing, Will Study Guide & Homework Help |publisher=eNotes.com |date= |accessdate=2013-03-28}}</ref> He remained with Mercury for two more albums, ''Moods'' in 1995 and ''Invitation Only'' in 1997, both of which sold well.<ref name=\"AMG\"/> ''All the Man You Need'' received a [[Grammy Award]] nomination for Best Traditional R&B Album in 2000. The album included \"When You Need Me\", a duet single with [[Chante Moore]].<ref>Billboard - 8 Jul 2000 - Page 24 \"released first single \"When You Need Me,\" a duet with MCA's Chante Moore\"</ref> In 2002, Downing received the International Association of African-American Music Diamond Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iaaam.com/IAAAMCelebrationPhotoGallery.html |title=International Association of African-American Music |publisher=Iaaam.com |date=2002-06-07 |accessdate=2013-03-28}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2006, Downing suffered from [[polymyositis]].<ref name=\"AMG\"/> Despite the debilitating aspects of the disease, he worked towards releasing a new album in 2010.<ref name=\"ABILITY\">{{cite web|url=http://abilitymagazine.com/Will_Downing.html |title=Will Downing Will Power |publisher=Abilitymagazine.com |date=2007-01-03 |accessdate=2013-03-28}}</ref> ''[[Love, Lust, & Lies: An Audio Novel]]'' was released in September that year.<ref name=\"AMG\"/> Beyond performing, Downing is a spokesperson for the [[American Stroke Association]]. On tour, he conducts the charity bowling event, Strike Against Stroke, to raise funds towards awareness and education in the African American community, which is disproportionately affected. The [[American Heart Association]] recognized Downing for his efforts, honoring him as a Celebrity Ambassador. He is also a keen photographer, and self-published the 2005 coffee table book ''Unveiled Series I''. He is a member of [[Omega Psi Phi]] fraternity. He has been married twice. He is currently married to his second wife. He has three children, including daughter Aja Downing. His stepbrother is former [[Boyz II Men]] member and musician [[Michael McCary]].\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Album details\n! colspan=\"5\"| Chart positions <ref name=Billboard_Biz>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f[0]=ts_chart_artistname%3AWill%20Downing&f[1]=ss_bb_type%3Achart_item&type=2&artist=Will%20Downing|title=Will Downing Charts Search|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=2017-06-10}}</ref><ref name=\"billboard\">{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=Will Downing|chart=all}}|title=Will Downing US chart history|publisher=billboard.com|accessdate=2017-06-10}}</ref><ref name=\"uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/_/will%20downing/|title=UK Charts > Will Downing|publisher=[[The Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=2017-06-10}}</ref>\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| [[Music recording sales certification|Certifications]] / Note\n|- style=\"font-size:smaller;\"\n! width=\"50\"| [[Billboard 200|US]]\n! width=\"50\"| [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums|R&B/<br>Hip-Hop]]\n! width=\"50\"| [[Billboard charts|Jazz]]\n! width=\"50\"| [[Billboard charts|Con.<br>Jazz]]\n! width=\"50\"| [[UK Albums Chart|UK]]\n|-\n| 1988\n| align=\"left\"| '''''Will Downing'''''\n* {{small|Released: March 1988}}\n* {{small|Label: [[Island Records|Island]]}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| 20\n|align=\"left\"| \n* [[British Phonographic Industry|BPI]]: Gold<ref name=\"bpi\">{{cite certification|region=United Kingdom|artist=Will Downing|accessdate=2017-06-10}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1989\n| align=\"left\"| '''''Come Together as One'''''\n* {{small|Released: October 24, 1989}}\n* {{small|Label: Island}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| 62\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| 36\n|align=\"left\"| \n|-\n| 1991\n| align=\"left\"| '''''A Dream Fulfilled'''''\n* {{small|Released: March 5, 1991}}\n* {{small|Label: Island}}\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| 22\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| \u2014\n|align=\"center\"| 43\n|align=\"left\"| \n|-\n| 1993\n| align=\"left\"| '''''Love's the Place to Be'''''\n