ive, digitized in 2007| page=[https://archive.org/details/speakerofhouseof00folluoft/page/337 337]}}</ref><br>[[John Jay]] (from December 10, 1778 until September 28, 1779)<ref name=Follett1909/><br>[[Samuel Huntington (Connecticut politician)|Samuel Huntington]] (from September 28, 1779)<ref name=Follett1909/>\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[History of the United States (1776\u20131789)]]\n* [[List of delegates to the Continental Congress]]\n* [[State cessions]]\n* [[Timeline of the American Revolution]]\n* [[United Colonies]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Adams, Willi Paul. ''The First American Constitutions: Republican Ideology and the Making of the State Constitutions in the Revolutionary Era.'' U. of North Carolina Press, 1980. {{ISBN|0-7425-2069-2}}\n* {{Cite book| first=H. James| last=Henderson| title=Party Politics in the Continental Congress| origyear=1974| year=2002| publisher=Rowman & Littlefield| isbn=0-8191-6525-5}}\n* Peter Force, ed. ''American Archives'' 9 vol 1837\u20131853, major compilation of documents 1774\u20131776. [https://web.archive.org/web/20070206214032/http://dig.lib.niu.edu/amarch/index.html online edition]\n* Kruman, Marc W. ''Between Authority and Liberty: State Constitution Making in Revolutionary America.'' U. of North Carolina Pr., 1997. {{ISBN|0-8078-4797-6}}\n* {{Cite book| first=Lynn| last=Montross| title=The Reluctant Rebels; the Story of the Continental Congress, 1774\u20131789| origyear=1950| year=1970| publisher=Barnes & Noble| isbn=0-389-03973-X| url-access=registration| url=https://archive.org/details/reluctantrebelss0000mont}}\n* Rakove, Jack N. ''The Beginnings of National Politics: An Interpretive History of the Continental Congress.'' Knopf, 1979. {{ISBN|0-8018-2864-3}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Commons category-inline|Continental Congress}}\n* [[Image:US-LOC-AmericanMemory-Logo.svg|44px|left]] [http://memory.loc.gov/ammem/amlaw/lwjclink.html Full text of ''Journals of the Continental Congress, 1774\u20131789'']<br>[http://memory.loc.gov/ammem/amlaw/lwdg.html Letters of Delegates to Congress, 1774-1789]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Succession box\n| title  = Second Continental Congress\n| before = [[First Continental Congress]]\n| years  = May 10, 1775 \u2013 March 1, 1781\n| after  = {{Nowrap|[[Congress of the Confederation]]}}}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{USAConfGov}}\n{{Pennsylvania during the American Revolutionary War}}\n{{American Revolutionary War|state=collapsed}}\n{{Federal Reserve System}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1775 establishments in the Thirteen Colonies]]\n[[Category:1781 disestablishments in the United States]]\n[[Category:Continental Congress|*]]\n[[Category:History of the United States government|Continental, second]]\n[[Category:History of Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:History of Baltimore]]\n[[Category:History of Lancaster, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:York, Pennsylvania]]\n[[Category:Provisional governments]]\n[[Category:United States Declaration of Independence]]\n", "name_user": "64.251.159.202", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eProvisional government)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Second_Continental_Congress"}
